# Libraries, language, and frameworks

## Stack

- **Java 21**, **Maven** multi-module, **JPMS** (`module-info.java` in every module).
- **Logging:** SLF4J only — never `System.out`, `System.err`, or JUL.
- Core library: **no** Spring, Quarkus, or web UI in `commons` / `client` / `server` production code.

## Approved usage by layer

| Layer | Use | Do not |
|-------|-----|--------|
| Protocol / framing | JDK, `commons` types | Client/server imports in `commons` |
| Client transport | JDK NIO, WebSocket APIs, SPI | Reach into consumer `internal` packages |
| Server channels | Vert.x (WebSocket), JDK NIO (TCP) | Expose `channels` / `session` in public API |
| Tests | JUnit 5, AssertJ, Awaitility, Testcontainers | `Thread.sleep()` for sync; raw broker URLs when `StompContainer` exists |
| Bridge | Kafka client (in `bridge/` only) | Kafka deps in core modules |
| Integrations | Spring / Quarkus in their modules only | Frameworks in core production code |
| Scripts | Bash (`set -euo pipefail`) or JBang | Python, Node, `.mjs` in `scripts/` |

## JPMS

- Export only intentional public API packages.
- Internal: `client.internal`, `server.channels`, `server.session`.
- SPI: update `module-info.java` **and** `META-INF/services/…`.
- Test reflective access: `opens` in test `module-info.java` only.

## Local development

```bash
mvn verify                                              # full gate (Docker)
mvn -Pfast -pl commons,client,server test               # fast loop
docker compose -f scripts/docker/docker-compose.yaml up # optional Artemis
```

Ports (compose): STOMP TCP **61613**, WebSocket **61614**, OpenWire **61616**, console **8161**.

Testcontainers reuse: `src/test/resources/testcontainers.properties`.

## CI and hooks

GitHub Actions: **bash** or **Maven** — not Python or Node runners. No `.py` files in the repository.

## Never

- Add `package.json` or bundlers to the library.
- Import `client.internal` or server internal packages from outside their module.
- Ship protocol changes without `commons` tests + integration test when client/server behaviour changes.
